frameDefinitions: A Part is considered to be a member of the set described by the Total.
This frame is about the static comparison of an Profiled_item to a Standard_item, often  with respect to some Attribute.
In this frame a Patient is in a state of having been broken into smaller pieces.  '
An Item which encompasses characteristics or types whose diversity is indicated by adducing a Limit1 and a Limit2 which differ considerably from each other.
In this frame a Fugitive presents himself or herself to the Authorities to be subject to the criminal process. '
As is usual for locative relations, the location of the Figure is specified as being inside a region defined relative to the Ground.

listRoleDefinitions: The complex multi-part entity of which a constituent <fen>Part</fen> is specified.
A subset of the <fen>Total</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the subset relation holds.
The <fen>Place</fen> at which the subset relation holds.
In active sentences, the <fen>Profiled_item</fen> is the grammatically more prominent one of the items that are compared and realized as  the subject. .
In active setnnces, the <fen>Standard_item</fen> is  the grammatically less prominent element, i.e. the object or an oblique.
This Frame Elements marks constituents that indicate in which respect Item-1 and Item-2 are equal to each other.
The <fen>Standard_attribute</fen> is used when the standard is a specific value on  a scale.
The <fen>Profiled_attribute</fen> is a particular value on a scale which is being compared to a <fen>Standard_item</fen> or <fen>Profiled_attribute</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Profiled_item</fen> rivals the <fen>Standard_item</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Profiled_item</fen> rivals the <fen>Standard_item</fen>.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity acted on and that undergoes a change.
The entity whose scalar property is specified.
The scalar property that the <fen>Item</fen> possesses.
The first-mentioned possibility of the range of variation.
The second item of the range of variation.
The range of positions on the scale that the <fen>Item</fen> occupies.
The <fen>Fugitive</fen> is wanted by the <fen>Authorities</fen> and turns himself or herself in to the <fen>Authorities</fen>.
The <fen>Authorities</fen> are the officials, government or otherwise, who are in charge of initiating the criminal process.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Fugitive</fen> surrenders.
The <fen>Place</fen> is the location where the surrendering occurs.

The <fen>Ground</fen> serves as a basis for describing the location of the <fen>Figure</fen>, as inside a region measured outward from the <fen>Ground</fen> and of a width specified by <fen>Distance</fen>.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is perceived as located relative to a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location.
This  role identifies the  <fen>Distance</fen> between the <fen>Ground</fen> and the borders of the region within which the <fen>Figure</fen> is located.
